# Agent: MCP-first Search

## Rule

For 1C project-source search, use project index/MCP tools before Grep/Glob when available.

## Priority

1. Metadata graph / code metadata / business search / object dossier.
2. Code index / search function / module structure / call hierarchy.
3. Retry with broader/narrower query or grep-like mode inside the index if tool supports it.
4. Only then native Grep/Glob, with a note why MCP/index did not return enough.

## Native Grep/Glob allowed immediately for

- Markdown/rules/docs.
- JSON/YAML/config files.
- logs/build artifacts.
- file already read in this session.
- non-1C source not indexed by MCP.

## Response note

If Grep/Glob was used on 1C project source, include one short line:

`MCP/index tried: <...>; fallback to Grep because <...>.`

